overview:
Andreas Saebjoernsen is a computer scientist and software entrepreneur. He originally hails from Norway as a physicist turned software engineer. He has a passion for social products that help people build trust and connect in real life.

Andy is an exceptionally talented engineer who likes designing conceptualized algorithms, by thinking through complex problems and distilling solutions to their essence, embracing constraints and writing beautiful code. He is a full-stack development expert comfortable developing applications in a variety of technology environments.

Andy is fluid in user interface engineering and front-end frameworks. He loves modeling database schema, user interfaces, and workflows with technology teams. Most of all he takes pride in building products that demonstrate high quality craftsmanship.

He is the cofounder of Founderly (an open source media project of founder stories) and Cosemble (a social platform for event ticketing). He received a B.S. in Physics from University of Oslo and he is currently a Ph.D. candidate in Computer Science at University of California, at Davis.
